rdf:Description.rdfs:label: GND ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: GND ID

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: VIAF ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: VIAF ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier for the Virtual International Authority File database [format: up to 22 digits]

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Bibliothèque nationale de France ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: Bibliothèque nationale de France ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier for the subject issued by BNF (Bibliothèque nationale de France). Format: 8 digits followed by a check-digit or letter, do not include the initial 'cb'.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: SELIBR ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: SELIBR ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier per National Library of Sweden Libris library catalog

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Biblioteca Nacional de España ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: Biblioteca Nacional de España ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier from the authority file of the Biblioteca Nacional de España. Format for persons: "XX" followed by 4 to 7 digits

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISNI
rdf:Description.schema:name: ISNI
rdf:Description.schema:description: International Standard Name Identifier for an identity. Format: 4 blocks of 4 digits separated by a space, first block is 0000

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Library of Congress authority ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: Library of Congress authority ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: Library of Congress name authority (persons, families, corporate bodies, events, places, works and expressions) and subject authority identifier [Format: 1-2 specific letters followed by 8-10 digits (see regex). For manifestations, use P1144]

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Libraries Australia ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: Libraries Australia ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier issued by the National Library of Australia (see also P1315 for the newer People Australia identifier). VIAF component. Format: 1-12 digits, removing leading zero-padding.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: IdRef ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: IdRef ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier for authority control in the French collaborative library catalog (see also P1025). Format: 8 digits followed by a digit or "X"

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: NKCR AUT ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: NKCR AUT ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier in the Czech National Authority Database (National Library of Czech Republic)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Freebase ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: Freebase ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier for a page in the Freebase database. Format: "/m/0" followed by 2 to 7 characters. For those starting with "/g/", use Google Knowledge Graph identifier (P2671)
